OUT! Caught. Emma de Broughe to Anesu Mushangwe. Length ball, driving, Edged in the air uncontrolled to cover, caught by O'Neil. South Australian Women have prevailed over ACT Meteors after a commanding display in all aspects of the game. Some handy late hitting by Barsby and Larosa set ACT a tough target to chase. It proved to be too steep as SA picked up wickets at regular intervals. Wellington picked up three wickets, as did de Broughe, remarkably bowling for the first time in the competition. Barsby is the Player of the Match for her contribution with the bat and ball.
